{"title_page": "Siren (TV series)", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 American drama television series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Siren\n| image = Siren Logo.jpg\n| alt = \n| genre = [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]<br>[[Thriller (genre)|Thriller]]<br>[[Fantasy (genre)|Fantasy]]<br>[[Mystery film|Mystery]]\n| creator = Eric Wald<br>[[Dean White (director)|Dean White]]\n| director =\n| composer = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Michael A. Levine]]\n*[[Anton Sanko]]\n}}\n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Alex Roe]]\n*[[Eline Powell]]\n*Ian Verdun\n*[[Rena Owen]]\n*Fola Evans-Akingbola\n*[[Sibongile Mlambo]]\n* Tiffany Lonsdale\n}}\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| num_seasons = 3<!-- Update only after a new season begins --> \n| num_episodes = 28<!-- Update only after a new episode debuts -->\n| list_episodes = #Episodes\n| executive_producer = {{Plainlist|\n*Emily Whitesell\n*Eric Wald\n*Dean White\n*Brad Luff\n*Nate Hopper\n*RD Robb\n*Michael Gans\n*Richard Register\n}}\n| producer = {{Plainlist|\n*Peter Lhotka\n*Heather Thomason\n}}\n| location = [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]]\n| cinematography = {{Plainlist|\n*Stephen Jackson\n*Mark Chow\n*Brian Pearson\n*Lindsay George\n}}\n| editor = \n| camera = [[Single-camera setup|Single-camera]]\n| runtime = 41\u201345 minutes\n| channel = [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]]\n| picture_format = \n| audio_format = \n| company = Stockton Drive Inc. <!--Shown on ending credits-->\n|distributor = [[Disney\u2013ABC Domestic Television]]\n|first_aired = {{Start date|2018|3|29}}\n|last_aired = {{End date|present}}\n|website = https://freeform.go.com/shows/siren\n}}\n'''''Siren''''' (formerly known as '''''The Deep'''''<ref name=\"TD\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/07/the-deep-mermaid-thriller-drama-picked-up-pilot-freeform-1201792249/|title=\u2018The Deep\u2019 Mermaid Thriller Drama Picked Up To Pilot By Freeform|work=Deadline Hollywood|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=July 26, 2016|accessdate=July 26, 2016}}</ref>) is an American television drama series that premiered on [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]] on March 29, 2018.<ref name=\"mermaid\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/10/siren-freeform-international-mermaid-day-premiere-date-1202184239/|title=Freeform\u2019s Mermaid Drama \u2018Siren\u2019 Gets Premiere Date, Casts Duo, Releases Clip|last=Ramos|first=Dino-Ray|date=October 7, 2017|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=January 25, 2018}}</ref> The first season included 10 episodes.<ref name=\"Siren\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/siren/listings/|title=Siren on Freeform|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|accessdate=March 30, 2018}}</ref> In May 2018, the series was renewed for a 16-episode second season which premiered on January 24, 2019.<ref name=\"S2premiere\"/> In May 2019, the series was renewed for a third season which premiered on April 2, 2020.<ref name=\"Season 3 Renewal\"/><ref name=\"S3PremiereDate\"/>\n\n==Plot==\nThe coastal town of Bristol Cove, Washington, known for its legend of once being home to [[Mermaid|mermaid]]s, is turned upside down when a mysterious young woman ([[Eline Powell]]) appears and begins wreaking havoc upon the small fishing town to look for her captured sister ([[Sibongile Mlambo]]) who was abducted at the hands of the local military. Marine biologists Ben ([[Alex Roe]]) and Maddie (Fola Evans-Akingbola) work together to find out who and what drove this primal hunter of the deep sea to land.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n===Main===\n* [[Alex Roe]] as Benjamin \"Ben\" Gregory Pownall, a marine biologist who helps Ryn and is entranced by her melodious, irresistibly hypnotic siren song and becomes her lover. \n* [[Eline Powell]] as Ryn Fisher, a strange young adult mermaid with a dark secret. She comes ashore in search of her sister who had been accidentally captured by fishermen of the ''North Star'' fishing vessel. \n* Ian Verdun as Xander McClure, a deep-sea fisherman who seeks to discover the truth about the existence of mermaids and mermen. \n* Fola Evans-Akingbola as Madalyn \"Maddie\" Bishop, a marine biologist and Ben's girlfriend in season one and two. She works at Bristol Cove Marine Research Center with Ben. Her step-father is the sheriff of Bristol Cove. Her estranged mother is Susan, who returns after five months in Season 2. Like Ben, Maddie is entranced by Ryn's melodious, irresistibly hypnotic siren song and becomes her lover.\n* [[Sibongile Mlambo]] as Donna (season 1), a mystical and deceptively powerful mermaid who is Ryn's older sister. She was unintentionally caught in a fishing net and taken by the military. She was killed, unintentionally, by Xander.\n* [[Rena Owen]] as Helen Hawkins, an eccentric woman who seems to know much more about the merfolk than she claims. It is revealed that she is descended from merfolk and shares ancestry with Ben and the other Pownalls. She eventually learns that she has a long-lost relative from the Marzdan family, most of whom are known as hybrids. She discovers that her mother Daphne was one of the merpeople/human hybrids who was promised to fellow hybrid Johnathon Rooney, but had chosen Helen's human father instead. This resulted in the death of Mr Hawkins a few weeks before Helen was born.\n* Tiffany Lonsdale as Tia (season 3),<ref name=\"TL\"/> a new mermaid from another colony/tribe of the northern seas around Bristol Cove, Washington. The human locals refer to her as \"sea monster\". Her intent on arriving on land is to coerce all other merpeople tribes and colonies to join her in putting an end to humans or perish by her wrath; somewhat similar to Katrina's motives.\n\n===Recurring===\n* Chad Rook as Chris Mueller,<ref>Chad Rook (@ChadRook) on Twitter\u2014[https://twitter.com/chadrook/status/864473477004140544 Twitter Confirmation of Chad Rook being part of Siren cast] (May 16, 2017)</ref> a fisherman who was taken to the military base after being injured by Donna.\n* Curtis Lum as Calvin, a fisherman who is also a friend and roommate of Xander.\n* [[Ron Yuan]] as Aldon Decker, an expert on mermaids that works for the military. He experimented on and became obsessed with, Donna. Decker was later found dead in the Season 1 finale after Donna's death having been subjected to the Siren song.\n* [[Gil Birmingham]] as Dale Bishop, the sheriff of the Bristol Cove Sheriff's Department and Maddie's stepfather. He is descended from the ancient [[Haida people]]. He is the third human to discover the existence of merpeople and becomes another ally.\n* [[Garcelle Beauvais]] as Susan Bishop (voiced season 1, season 2),<ref>Garcelle Beauvais on Deadline [https://deadline.com/2018/07/siren-garcelle-beauvais-recur-season-2-freeform-drama-1202434224/] (July 26, 2018)</ref> Maddie's estranged mother and Dale's ex-wife who tries to make amends with her estranged family.\n* [[David Cubitt]] as Ted Pownall, Ben's father, head of the town's fishery industry and whose great-great-great-grandfather Charles first discovered merpeople in the mid-1800s. \n* [[Sarah-Jane Redmond]] as Elaine Pownall, Ben's mother, who became paralyzed after a boating accident a decade earlier. She is eventually given renewed treatment from none other than aquatic stem cells from Ryn's mermaid DNA.\n* [[Tammy Gillis]] as Marissa Staub, the deputy of the Bristol Cove Sheriff's Department.\n* [[Hannah Levien]] as Janine, Calvin's girlfriend who is a bartender at the Anchor.\n* [[Andrew Jenkins (actor)|Andrew Jenkins]] as Doug Pownall, Ben's older brother.\n* Anthony Harrison as Admiral Harrison, the head of the military base in Season 1.\n* Natalee Linez as Nicole Martinez, a military replacement for Decker who becomes the girlfriend of Xander. She continues Decker\u2019s research on mermaids.\n* Luc Roderique as Ian Sutton, an environmentalist and news reporter who supports Ben and Maddie on bringing down the Klesco Oil Company for destroying marine life and their aquatic ecosystems in search of natural oil from the depths of the seas. He soon starts to get suspicious of Ryn and tries to take her, only to drown in the water after driving off a cliff.\n*David Kaye as Jerry, who works at Bristol Cove Marine Research Center along with Ben and Maddie. He is the one who makes fake IDs for the merpeople (thereby officially naming them) in \"Oil and Water\"; completely unaware of their true selves and nature.\n\n===Merpeople===\nBesides sisters Ryn and Donna, the following mermaid and mermen characters are''':'''\n* Aylya Marzolf as Katrina, a mermaid alpha leader who was twice defeated by Ryn in combat. She is the most fierce and independent of the colony, displaying brute force against both humans and mermaids if need be.\n* Sedale Threatt Jr. as Levi, a [[Merman]] warrior. He is mentored by Ben and considers him and Maddie his friends. Levi killed Xander's father Sean during a attack on humans in the ocean during season 1.\n* Hugo Ateo as Frank, better known as Sarge, a merman protector who becomes infatuated with Helen Hawkins and she with him. He dies during the attack on Klesco Oil Company' oil platform. Many months later, Helen finds a way to contact his essence with the help of Eliza.\n* Millan Tesfazgi as Cami, a mermaid who is the daughter of the late Donna and niece of Ryn. She seeks revenge for her mother's death.\n* Alvina August as Viv, a brown-skinned mermaid from Ryn and Donna\u2019s colony who is a close friend of Eliza.\n* Georgia Scarlet Waters as Eliza, a blonde mermaid from Ryn and Donna\u2019s colony. She develops a kind of romantic attraction towards Rick Marzdan. She is one of few mermaids who are healers.\n* Katie Keough as Hunter, a tall olive-skinned mermaid from Ryn and Donna's colony. She is known as a fierce hunter and first appears on land during mating season.\n*Elderly Mermaid, first appeared in \"No North Star\" she was discovered by Katrina, who was hunting for food with Cami, inside a plane crash. She reached out toward Katrina and looked sickly. \n* Tiffany Lonsdale as Tia, debuting in the Season 3 premiere, she is a mermaid from another colony who competes with Ryn in putting an end to all humans by forcing every colony and tribe to join her or face death.\n\n===Human/Merpeople Hybrids===\nWhen humans and merpeople secretly mated over the centuries, they produce children with a varied blend of bloodlines, from one-eighth, to one-quarter, to half of both species . In addition to Helen, the following characters are:\n*Daphne Hawkins, the late mother of Helen who had a very close kinship with John Rooney and was betrothed to him to keep the merpeople-human bloodline going. She had fallen in love with a human man, which was forbidden and considered a betrayal of the tribe. In a desperate attempt to hide, she had written to Ted Pownall's grandmother and asked if she and her husband could stay in the family cottage since she was pregnant with Helen. Unfortunately, Caleb Pownall was enraged and started a fire that killed Mr. Hawkins immediately. \n*Jonathon \"John\" Rooney, the intended of Daphne who was passed over for Mr. Hawkins. He immediately recognizes Helen, stating that her voice is exactly like her late mother's. \n* [[Brendan Fletcher]] as Rick Marzdan, a long-lost blood relative of Helen. Just like her, he has merfolk blood in him.\n* [[Caroline Cave]] as Elizabeth \"Beth\" Marzdan, a long-lost blood relative of Helen and the estranged sister of Rick who leads a community of human/merpeople hybrids.\n* [[Daniel Cudmore]] as Ryan, a human/merman hybrid, husband of Leena, and father of Meredith, who is associated with Beth and can act hostile towards the Pownalls for their connection to Charles Pownall.\n*Kaaren de Zilva as Dr. Leena, personal physician and secretly the wife of Ryan and mother of Meredith. She secretly injected the embryo of Ryn's unborn child into her daughter in an attempt to have a full-blooded merperson grandchild of her own.\n*Kiomi Pyke as Meredith, the secret daughter of Ryan and Dr. Leena who had the embryo of Ryn's unborn child implanted into her uterus in order for her parents to have a full-blooded merperson grandchild of they own. She expressed doubts at what would happen to her carrying a child that is not hers.\n\n===Guest===\n* [[Brian Anthony Wilson]] as Sean McClure, Xander's father and captain of the fishing motorboat ''The North Star''. He was killed by Levi in \"Dead in the Water\" per orders of the alpha mermaid Katrina. Months later, his corpse accidentally resurfaces. \n*Patti McClure, wife of the late Captain Sean McClure and mother of Xander. Debuting in \"Being Human\" she expressed her sorrow at her husband's sudden demise by \"getting tangled in a fishing net\" and blamed Ted Pownall for letting his greed for money lead, if unintentionally, to such a tragedy. Many months later, \"Entrapment\", she received news that her late husband's corpse had been found and now has found peace.\n\n==Episodes==\n===Series overview===\n{{Series overview\n| color1     = #5DC1B9\n| link1      = #Season 1 (2018)\n| episodes1  = 10\n| start1     = {{Start date|2018|3|29}}\n| end1       = {{End date|2018|5|24}}\n\n| color2     = #1B2A36\n| link2      = #Season 2 (2019)\n| episodes2  = 16\n| start2     = {{Start date|2019|1|24}}\n| end2       = {{End date|2019|8|1}}\n\n| color3     = #005F6C\n| link3      = #Season 3 (2020)\n| episodes3  = 13\n| start3     = {{Start date|2020|4|2}}\n| end3       =\n}}\n\n===Season 1 (2018)===\n{{Episode table |background=#5DC1B9 |overall=5 |season=5 |title=17 |director=11 |writer=27 |airdate=10 |viewers=9 |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Pilot\n |DirectedBy      = [[Scott Stewart (director)|Scott Stewart]]\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Eric Wald & [[Dean White (director)|Dean White]]|t=Eric Wald|tfirst=y}}\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|3|29}}\n |Viewers         = 0.87<ref name=\"Premiere\">{{cite web|url=h