mber 20, 2018}}</ref> On May 14, 2019, the series was renewed for a third season which premiered on April 2, 2020.<ref name=\"Season 3 Renewal\">{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/05/14/siren-season-3-renewed-freeform-premiere-date/|title=Siren Renewed for Season 3|last=Swift|first=Andy|work=TVLine|date=May 14, 2019|accessdate=May 14, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"S3PremiereDate\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/siren-season-3-premiere-date-freeform-1202833806/|title='Siren' Gets Season 3 Premiere Date At Freeform; First-Look Photo \u2013 TCA|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=January 17, 2020|accessdate=January 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nOn August 24, 2016, [[Eline Powell]] joined the cast in the role of Po (renamed Ryn) and [[Rena Owen]] as Helen.<ref name=\"cast\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/08/the-deep-pilot-eline-powell-rena-owen-claws-jason-antoon-1201807868/|title=\u2018The Deep\u2019 Pilot Casts Eline Powell & Rena Owen; \u2018Claws\u2019 Adds Jason Antoon|work=Deadline Hollywood|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=August 24, 2016|accessdate=August 24, 2016}}</ref> On September 26, 2016, Ian Verdun joined the cast in the role of Xander, followed by a few days of [[Alex Roe]] and Fola Evans-Akingbola in the roles of Ben and Maddie, respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/09/the-deep-ian-verdun-freeform-mermaid-thriller-drama-pilot-series-regular-1201826089/|title=\u2018The Deep\u2019: Ian Verdun Joins Freeform\u2019s Mermaid Thriller Drama Pilot|work=Deadline Hollywood|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=September 26, 2016|accessdate=September 26, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"main cast\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/10/the-deep-alex-roe-fola-evans-akingbola-cast-freeform-pilot-eline-powell-1201831760/|title=\u2018The Deep\u2019: Alex Roe & Fola Evans-Akingbola Round Out Cast Of Freeform Pilot|work=Deadline Hollywood|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=October 6, 2016|accessdate=October 6, 2016}}</ref> [[Chad Rook]] announced on May 16, 2017 via [[twitter]] that he will be in the series playing Chris Mueller. On July 26, 2017, it was announced that [[Sibongile Mlambo]] joined the cast as regular as Donna.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/07/siren-sibongile-mlambo-cast-series-regular-freeform-drama-1202136322/|title=\u2018Siren\u2019: Sibongile Mlambo Cast As Series Regular In Freeform Drama|work=Deadline Hollywood|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=July 26, 2017|accessdate=July 26, 2017}}</ref> On August 14, 2019, Tiffany Lonsdale was cast as a new series regular for the third season.<ref name=\"TL\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/siren-tiffany-lonsdale-series-regular-season-3-freeform-series-1202667878/|title='Siren': Tiffany Lonsdale Set As New Series Regular For Season 3 Of Freeform Series|work=Deadline Hollywood|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=August 14, 2019|accessdate=August 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Music ===\n[[Michael A. Levine]] is the former composer of ''Siren'''s score.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2017/10/08/michael-a-levine-scoring-freeforms-siren/|title=Michael A. Levine Scoring Freeform\u2019s \u2018Siren\u2019 {{!}}  Film Music Reporter|website=filmmusicreporter.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-30}}</ref><ref name=\"scifitalk.com\">{{Cite news|url=https://scifitalk.com/2018/04/04/podcast-siren-composer-michael-a-levine/|title=PODCAST: Siren Composer Michael A. Levine|date=2018-04-04|access-date=2018-05-30|language=en-US}}</ref> The haunting and seductive ''Siren Call'' was written and composed by Levine and performed by singer/songwriter Mariana Barreto. Throughout the composition cycle, Levine incorporated the sounds of the tenor violin, octave viola (ciola), and the [[gusli]].<ref name=\"scifitalk.com\"/> A soundtrack release date has yet to be announced by [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fearsmag.com/post/174186345751/siren-renewed-for-season-2-at-freeform|title=Siren Renewed for Season 2 at Freeform|website=Fears Magazine|access-date=2018-05-30}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nThe pilot was filmed in October 2016, in [[Vancouver]] [[British Columbia]], Canada.<ref name=\"Filming\"/> Pre-production started on July 26, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://freeform.go.com/shows/siren/news/freeforms-siren-dives-into-production|title=Freeform's Siren Dives Into Production|publisher=[[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]]|accessdate=July 26, 2017}}</ref> The official shooting of the remaining episodes began on August 4, 2017,<ref>{{cite tweet|user=RenaOwen|author=Rena Owen|number=893357163124359168|title=Siren Season 1 Starts Filming in Vancouver (link: http://www.whatsfilming.ca/2017/08/02/siren-season-1-starts-filming-vancouver/) whatsfilming.ca/2017/08/02/sir\u2026 via @whatsfilming|date=August 4, 2017|accessdate=August 4, 2017}}</ref> and continued until November 22, 2017.<ref name=\"Filming\">{{cite web|url=http://www.whatsfilming.ca/2017/08/02/siren-season-1-starts-filming-vancouver/|title=Siren Season 1 Starts Filming in Vancouver|website=whatsfilming.ca|date=August 2, 2017|accessdate=August 2, 2017}}</ref> Filming for season 3 began on August 1, 2019 and ended on December 16, 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dgc.ca/assets/Uploads/BritishColumbia/AvailsProductionLists/Documents/Production-List.pdf|title=DGC BC Production List|work=[[Directors Guild of Canada]]|date=July 4, 2019|accessdate=July 4, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190704023715/https://www.dgc.ca/assets/Uploads/BritishColumbia/AvailsProductionLists/Documents/Production-List.pdf|archivedate=July 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Marketing===\nThe [[trailer (promotion)|trailer]] was released on April 19, 2017, the same day it was picked up.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2017/04/19/freeform-trailers-the-bold-type-siren-video/|title=Freeform Releases First Trailers for Magazine Drama The Bold Type, Mermaid Thriller Siren \u2014 Watch|last=Swift|first=Andy|publisher=[[TVLine]]|date=April 17, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> The first episode was shown at the [[New York Comic Con]] in October 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://talknerdywithus.com/2017/10/09/interviews-with-the-cast-and-producers-of-siren-at-nycc-2017/|title=Interviews with the Cast and Producers of Siren at NYCC 2017|last=Streaty|first=Christian|website=talknerdywithus|date=October 9, 2017|accessdate=October 9, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical response===\nSiren has been well-received by critics. On the [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the series has an approval rating of 94% based on 18 reviews, with an average rating of 8.0/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''Siren'' turns traditional lore on its tail with a unique, well-paced show that presents dangerous, violent mythical creatures in a surprisingly empathetic and exciting light.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/siren/s01/ |title=''Siren'': Season 1 (2018) |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=January 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\n====Season 1====\n{{Television episode ratings\n| noshare  = y\n\n| title1   = [[#ep1|Pilot]]\n| date1    = March 29, 2018\n| rs1      = 0.3\n| viewers1 = 0.87<ref name=\"Premiere\"/>\n| dvr1     = 0.3\n| dvrv1    = 0.83\n| total1   = 0.6\n| totalv1  = 1.70<ref name=\"PremiereDVR\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/dvr-ratings/cable-live-7-ratings-for-march-26-april-1-2018/|title='Siren' premiere doubles in cable Live +7 ratings for March 26-April 1|last=Porter|first=Rick|date=April 11, 2018|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=April 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\n| title2   = [[#ep2|The Lure]]\n| date2    = March 29, 2018\n| rs2      = 0.3\n| viewers2 = 0.87<ref name=\"Premiere\"/>\n| dvr2     = 0.3\n| dvrv2    = 0.77\n| total2   = 0.6\n| totalv2  = 1.64<ref name=\"PremiereDVR\"/>\n\n| title3   = [[#ep3|Interview With a Mermaid]]\n| date3    = April 5, 2018\n| rs3      = 0.2\n| viewers3 = 0.62<ref name=\"